Officer: Sigh~ How long will this war continue?

Young man Luid: I don't think Lord Agnos will ever give up
on conquering Tarasa.

forced into this. It's only natural for us as imperial

Officer: What are you fighting for? Is it for the expansion
of territory, or is it your duty as a citizen?
Young man Luid: ...It's for Queen Caron's sake.

Officer: That's great! Fighting for the sake of our

Officer: The ship should be coming soon. A young guy like

00_Black

There was nothing more shocking to Luid than his own mother
disappearing from home and becoming the wife of King Agnos.
Nevertheless, Luid believed that there must be some
circumstances behind his mother's actions.

Luid threw himself into the Second Tarasa War, which had
claimed many lives, in order to be of some help to his
mother. However, Luid experienced hell on the battlefield
and lost many comrades.

Luid came to believe that the reason he was able to survive
was because he made daily efforts for the sake of his
mother. No, he couldn't maintain his sanity amidst the
aftermath of the war if he didn't think that way.

Luid's pure feelings towards his mother had become a curse,
binding him, and Caron's presence had infiltrated every
aspect of his actions. Luid continued to chase after the
illusion of his radiant mother.
While being fully aware that it was an illusion.
